::Shadow Wing::

She knew that this game was more than a game.  It was a test.  She was 
finding out what he could do.  And he was seeing what she was capable of.  
She really didn't like tricking him like that.  But she wanted him to know 
that She wasn't a feather brain.(bird joke) She wanted him to know that she 
could think when she had to and let instinct take over when nessessary.  She 
stopped at a brach about 20 feet off the ground and perched for a moment. 
She looked up into a tree near her's and saw another bird. It was a nice, 
fat crow.
"How do you like your crow? Rare, Medium or Well done?"
She didn't give him time to answer the question.  she swooped up and caught 
the crow that was sitting in another tree. She flew down and dropped it 
infront of Lunarpine.

"Sorry for the dirty trick I pulled. I'll be 'it' again if you want."
She pushed the crow closer to him. "Peace offering?"
